column168: AT APPROXIMATELY 4:40 AM ON MONDAY, FEBRUARY 17, 1986 WHILE THE A-2 ACCA YA RD JOB ASSIGNMENT WAS WORKING OUT A CUT OF CARS THAT HAD ARRIVED ON TRAIN 4 11 AT 1:55 AM, MR. T.P. HUNTER, BRAKEMAN, WAS SPLASHED IN THE FACE WITH SUL FURIC ACID FROM CAR 413102 WHICH WAS LEAKING AROUND THE DOME.  MR. HUNTER W AS SENT TO RICHMOND MEMORIAL HOSPITAL EMERGENCY ROOM FOR TREATMENT WHERE HE WAS TREATED AND RELEASED. CAR CSX 413102 WAS SHIPPED BY TEXACO CHEMICAL AT REYBOLD, DELAWARE DESTINED TO ALLIED CHEMICAL CORPORATION AT HOPEWELL, VIRGINIA.  CAR WAS PUT IN NUMB ER 16 TRACK NORTH YARD AT ACCA TO AWAIT DISPOSITION. CHEMTREC WAS NOTIFIED AT APPROXIMATELY 6:20 AM, FEBRUARY 17, 1986, REGARDIN G THIS INCIDENT.  AT APPROXIMATELY 7:30 AM, FEBRUARY 17, 1986, MR. SCHAEFER WITH TEXACO CHEMICAL IN NEW YORK CALLED AND ADVISED THAT MR. CAUDILL WITH TEXACO AT REYBOLD, DELAWARE WOULD CONTACT US TO ADVISE WHAT HAD TO BE DONE. MR. CAUDILL CALLED AT 8:50 AM AND REQUESTED THAT WE HOLD THE CAR UNTIL HE COULD COME DOWN AND PERSONALLY INSPECT THE CAR TO DETERMINE IF CAR WAS NOT PROPERLY SEALED WHEN SHIPPED OR IF RUBBER GASKET AROUND DOME WAS WORN.  MR CAUDILL REPORTED TO ACCA AT APPROXIMATELY 10:00 AM, FEBRUARY 18, 1986 AND MADE INSPECTION OF CAR CSX 413102.  CAR WAS FOUND TO HAVE A RUPTURED PRESSU RE DISC.  CAR SPECIFICATIONS CALLED FOR A 100 POUND PRESSURE DISC BUT CAR C ONTAINED A 60 POUND PRESSURE DISC.  MR CAUDILL DID NOT HAVE A DISC WITH HIM AND HE CONTACTED ALLIED CHEMICAL AT HOPEWELL AND THEY RESPONDED WITH DISC. DISC WAS EXCHANGED IN CAR AND CAR WAS MADE READY FOR FORWARDING AT 1:20 PM, FEBRUARY 18. CAR WAS FORWARDED TO HOPEWELL THE MORNING OF FEBRUARY 19.
